<subsection xml:id="subsec-angle-properties-of-polgons">
        <title>Angle Properties of Polgons</title>

        <p>
            In Grade 7 you learnt about properties of angles in a polygon; number of sides of polygons,
             interior angles of the polygons and the relationship between sides of polygons and interior angles.
        </p>
        <p>
            Here is a summary of what you learned from Grade 7
        </p>

        <p>
        <term>In order to find Number of right angles and the sum of interior angles of any polygon:</term>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Identify the number of sides (<m>n</m>) of the regular polygon.
                    </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p>
                        Work out how many triangles could be created within the polygon by drawing lines from a single vertex to all the other vertices
                    </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p>
                        Multiply the number of triangles in the polygon by <m>180^\circ</m> to find the sum of the interior angles of the polygon.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p> 

